Finance Minister Enoch Godongwana spoke with eNCA's Devan Murugan about his maiden speech. Courtesy of #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Finance Minister Enoch Godongwana says draft legislation proposing offering partial access to retirement funds, will be published for comment around mid-year. Godongwana says this will encourage the preservation of the bulk of individual retirement savings. Explainer: Early access to retirement savings is a risk The minister tabled his budget speech on Wednesday. He said "changes have been proposed to these regulations to enable greater investment in infrastructure by these funds. READ: Treasury to table pension system amendments for public comment "After consultation on these changes, the amendments will be gazetted next month." "Government has also proposed a fundamental restructuring of the retirement system for individuals to allow for greater preservation and partial access to funds through a “two-pot” system." "Part of this proposal includes the possibility of short-term access, which would be dependent on the approval by trustees of each fund... I will make the law which makes allows trustees to make the decision."